observationText: Nf1+/- mice exhibit cognitive deficits and serve as an important therapeutic model when crossed with p53 mutant mice to study malignant peripheral nerve sheath tumors.
Nf1+/- mice have reduced neurofibromin levels compared to wild-type mice.
Nf1+/- mice develop caf√©-au-lait macules and neurofibromas, which are classic phenotypes of neurofibromatosis type 1 in humans.
Nf1+/- mice exhibit initial learning delays in the T-maze task, hesitance to interact with novel objects, hyperactivity, and anxiety-like behaviors.
